Sentencas: Mixed ionic and electronic conduction (MIEC) in the composite cathode can alter oxygen stoichiometry and other physiochemical properties, eventually promoting the electrocatalytic functionalities for oxygen reduction reac-tion (ORR) at low operational temperatures (<650 degrees C).
Titulo: Tuning ORR electrocatalytic functionalities in CGFO-GDC composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here, we demonstrate a composite cathode of CoGd0.8Fe1.80O4 /Gd0.10Ce0.9O2-delta (CGFO-GDC), which delivers low electrode polarization resistance of 0.60 omega cm2 at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Tuning ORR electrocatalytic functionalities in CGFO-GDC composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The best-performing sample CGFO-GDC exhbits the peak power density (PPD) of 611-343 mW cm-2 at 550-470 degrees C under a fuel cell conditions.
Titulo: Tuning ORR electrocatalytic functionalities in CGFO-GDC composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, durability measurement verifies CGFO-GDC as a chemically stable cathode with improved ORR catalytic functionality.
Titulo: Tuning ORR electrocatalytic functionalities in CGFO-GDC composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Additionally, first principle calculations using density function theory (DFT) were also conducted to analyze the ion diffusion mechanism of fabricated CGFO-GDC cathode.
Titulo: Tuning ORR electrocatalytic functionalities in CGFO-GDC composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our findings certify that introducing ionic conducting GDC into CGFO sample improves the catalytic functionalities.
Titulo: Tuning ORR electrocatalytic functionalities in CGFO-GDC composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As a result, the composite CGFO-GDC based SOFC delivers minimum electrode polari-zation resistance with improved power output owing to its enhanced oxygen vacancies and fast catalytic re-actions at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Tuning ORR electrocatalytic functionalities in CGFO-GDC composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
